(7, 1, '2012-05-07 08:01:03', '2012-05-07 08:01:03', 'We''re really lucky here in little old Wellington, New Zealand. With Indian curries that beat anything from London''s Brick Lane, a Southeast Asian food scene that does Asia proud, great produce and farmers markets, superb wines, world class bakeries, and of course some of the best fish and chips in the world, we''re fortunate to have some of the best food in the world. So we feel that it''s about time that Wellington stood up and proudly took its place as the food capitol of New Zealand.\r\n\r\nWe get pretty sick of professional food writers who have been in the game for decades, writing about our local food with the passion of an office worker writing about their pencil collection. If someone plasters their face all over their reviews, how can they possibly expect to get non-preferential service from the restaurants they visit? How can they expect to have the real foodie experience?\r\n\r\nWouldn''t you much rather read food a food blog by real Wellington foodies who love food, who don''t get paid to write about it, who do it simply for the love of our local restaurant and cafe scene? I know I would. \r\n\r\nSo put the stuffed shirt away and tuck in to some real Wellington food writing.\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="author">\r\n<h3>Mike</h3>\r\nA long time Wellingtonian and self-confessed curry nut. I love Indian and Malaysian cuisines and any kind of street food. A fine dining and wine fan too - but loves a good steak and cheese pie as much as the next person.\r\n\r\nTop 3 Wellington dishes:\r\n<ol><li>\r\n<strong>Lamb Chetty Nadu - Temptation Indian Restaurant, Newtown.</strong><br />\r\nA fiery mix of hot chunks of lamb mixed with coconut flavours. Arguably the best curry in Wellington from one of the cities many hidden curry shop gems. Recommended kiwi hot - not over the top and complimates the flavours perfectly.\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Filet Mignon - Green Parrot, Taranaki Street.</strong><br />\r\nThe Green Parrot is an institution - a blast from the past in the best possible way. This dish comes with two (TWO!) massive steaks wrapped in bacon along with their standard massive plate of chips and salad. Epic.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chicken Rendang - KK Malaysia, Ghuznee Street.</strong><br />\r\nMost of the many Malaysian restaurants around Wellington do a variation of this popular dish, but for my money KK Malaysia is the best and most authentic Malaysian and tasty restaurant in town.\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id="sites">\r\n\r\n</div>', 'About', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about', '', '', '2012-05-27 05:17:16', '2012-05-27 05:17:16', '', 0, 'http://wellykai.co.nz/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
