(32, 1, '2012-05-07 08:40:03', '2012-05-07 08:40:03', '<div class="author">\r\n<h3>Mike</h3>\r\nA long time Wellingtonian and self-confessed curry nut. I love Indian and Malaysian cuisines and any kind of street food. A fine dining and wine fan too - but loves a good steak and cheese pie as much as the next person.\r\n\r\nTop 3 Wellington dishes:\r\n<ol><li>\r\n<strong>Lamb Chetty Nadu - Temptation Indian Restaurant, Newtown.</strong><br />\r\nA fiery mix of hot chunks of lamb mixed with coconut flavours. Arguably the best curry in Wellington from one of the cities many hidden curry shop gems. Recommended kiwi hot - not over the top and complimates the flavours perfectly.\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Filet Mignon - Green Parrot, Taranaki Street.</strong><br />\r\nThe Green Parrot is an institution - a blast from the past in the best possible way. This dish comes with two (TWO!) massive steaks wrapped in bacon along with their standard massive plate of chips and salad. Epic.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chicken Rendang - KK Malaysia, Ghuznee Street.</strong><br />\r\nMost of the many Malaysian restaurants around Wellington do a variation of this popular dish, but for my money KK Malaysia is the best and most authentic Malaysian and tasty restaurant in town.\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id="sites">\r\n\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-9', '', '', '2012-05-07 08:40:03', '2012-05-07 08:40:03', '', 7, 'http://wellykai.co.nz/2012/05/7-revision-9/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(33, 1, '2012-05-07 09:08:42', '2012-05-07 09:08:42', '<div id="aboutus">\r\nWe kind of get sick of Wellington food writers who have been in the game for years, writing about our local food with the passion of an office worker writing about their pencil collection. If you plaster your face all over your reviews, how can you possibly expect to get non-preferential service from the restaurants they visit?\r\n\r\nWouldn''t you much rather read food a food blog by real Wellington foodies who love food, who don''t get paid to write about, but do it simply for the love of our local restaurant and cafe scene? I know I would. Put the stuffed shirt away and tuck in to some real Wellington food writing.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="author">\r\n<h3>Mike</h3>\r\nA long time Wellingtonian and self-confessed curry nut. I love Indian and Malaysian cuisines and any kind of street food. A fine dining and wine fan too - but loves a good steak and cheese pie as much as the next person.\r\n\r\nTop 3 Wellington dishes:\r\n<ol><li>\r\n<strong>Lamb Chetty Nadu - Temptation Indian Restaurant, Newtown.</strong><br />\r\nA fiery mix of hot chunks of lamb mixed with coconut flavours. Arguably the best curry in Wellington from one of the cities many hidden curry shop gems. Recommended kiwi hot - not over the top and complimates the flavours perfectly.\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Filet Mignon - Green Parrot, Taranaki Street.</strong><br />\r\nThe Green Parrot is an institution - a blast from the past in the best possible way. This dish comes with two (TWO!) massive steaks wrapped in bacon along with their standard massive plate of chips and salad. Epic.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chicken Rendang - KK Malaysia, Ghuznee Street.</strong><br />\r\nMost of the many Malaysian restaurants around Wellington do a variation of this popular dish, but for my money KK Malaysia is the best and most authentic Malaysian and tasty restaurant in town.\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id="sites">\r\n\r\n</div>', 